Fetch Delphi's ILI nowcast

Source: R/endpoints.R
nowcast.Rd

API docs: https://cmu-delphi.github.io/delphi-epidata/api/nowcast.html.

nowcast(locations, epiweeks)

Arguments

locations

character vector. The locations to fetch.

epiweeks

timeset. The epiweeks to fetch.

Value

epidata_call

Details

Obtains information on outpatient inluenza-like-illness (ILI) from Delphi's epidemiological data

The full list of location inputs can be accsssed at https://github.com/cmu-delphi/delphi-epidata/blob/main/src/acquisition/fluview/fluview_locations.py.

Examples

# \donttest{
nowcast(locations = "ca", epiweeks = epirange(201201, 201301)) %>% fetch_classic()
